WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'BBBubbles' is a Workbench game where the goal is to burst as
many coloured bubbles on the game board as possible. But in order
to burst, two or more neighbouring bubbles have to be of the same
size. As you can guess, the more bubbles that blow up, and if they
are all of the same colour, the more points you get.

  To complicate matters a bit more, all the unselected bubbles are
in white so you cannot know what colours the bubbles will have, so
you have to click on those white bubbles to reveal their colours.

  As bubbles burst, they are then removed from the game board and
new white bubbles will appear in the empty spaces. Watch out for
the 'Bubble-O-Meter' indicated by a white bubble at the upper
right of the board. If that bubble gets smaller, that means there
are few neighbouring bubbles of the same size; if it blows up, the
game is over...

  Have fun!

